#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/util/pickle_support.py:7
msgid ""
"This module generates support for pickling vtkDataObjects from python. It "
"needs to be imported specifically in order to work:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/util/pickle_support.py:10
msgid "import vtkmodules.util.pickle_support"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/util/pickle_support.py:12
msgid ""
"Once imported however, the pickling of data objects is very straightforward. "
"Here is an example using poly data:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/util/pickle_support.py:15
msgid ""
"sphereSrc = vtkSphereSource() sphereSrc.Update() pickled = pickle."
"dumps(sphereSrc.GetOutput()) unpickled = pickle.loads(pickled) "
"print(unpickled) *description of sphere data set*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/util/pickle_support.py:22
msgid ""
"The underlying serialization of the vtkDatObjects is based on the marshaling "
"capabilities found in vtkCommunicator. Importing this module adds entries "
"for the most common data objects in the global dispatch table used by "
"pickle. NumPy is required as well since the -serialized data object gets "
"pickled as a numpy array."
msgstr ""

